field_demo_data_milestone_update.value: The weekly Federation staff bulletin, weekly e-mails to parents from both schools and half termly parental newsletter have been established since Easter and have been well received.  The last issues of these were heavily loaded with information and news demonstrating a movement from earlier in the year where news items were regularly asked for and more work was required in extracting news from across both schools.  Ensuring all staff and parents read all communications is an area of focus going forwards.  Parents Forum was established in the spring term and ran on a termly basis at both schools.  Attendance at the summer term forum for Booker Park parents was very well attended (14 parents) but not so for Stocklake parents (3 parents).

field_demo_data_milestone_update.value: The restructure process has been started and has been very successful.  The substantive deputy headteacher role has been appointed to from the 3 postholders at risk, with a satisfactory outcome in relation to the other two.  This has also allowed the recruitment and appointment of two assistant headteachers for Booker Park at the end of term one due to start in January, the other an internal candidate to start in April 2023 upon the completion of her maternity leave.  An assistant headteacher was successfully recruited to at Stocklake Park to replace Sophie who leaves at the end of 2021-22.

field_demo_data_milestone_update.value: Team Leader roles at Stocklake Park were highly sought after and were recruited to.  There was less demand for the roles at Booker Park but two roles were filled through existing TLR holders who essentially held this role already.  Additionally two further positions were filled through normal recruitment, with one starting in September and the other following a return from maternity at Easter 2023.  Following further discussions it is highly likely that a further internal candidate will apply and be appointed in the first few weeks of the autumn term 2023, and there are a number of possibilities for other internal promotions once the new teachers come in from September.  Whilst there is some shortfall to make up in the autumn term 2022, this is less challenge than has been required over the current and previous academic years from absence at deputy headteacher level.
